{
  "texts": [
    "These organoids recapitulate the complexities of neural development, offering insights into health and diseases (Avansini et al., 2022).",
    "The in vitro system allows for drug testing, intervention studies, and close observation of potential side effects.",
    "Organoid models support experiments and correlative microscopy in multimodal platforms, enabling comprehensive characterizations of entire samples in vivo.",
    "This approach represents a significant stride in neurobiology and drug development.",
    "Neural tracing using viral vectors and X-ray markers offers precise tools to investigate neural connections and circuitry, enhancing imaging capabilities for detailed visualization and mapping of neural structures."
  ]
}